cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.GR, cs.RO 

This paper is likely to belong to the Computer Vision (cs.CV) sub-category as it deals with semantic segmentation of aerial imagery using convolutional neural networks. The use of deep learning models also suggests that it could belong to the Machine Learning (cs.LG) and Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. The fact that the imagery is remotely sensed suggests that it could also belong to the Graphics (cs.GR) sub-category. Finally, the use of feedback loops and intermediate supervision suggests that it could belong to the Robotics (cs.RO) sub-category as well.
